        "body": "\n\n## Bug Description\n\nThe \"here\" hyperlink in the **Acknowledgements** section of the [Related Software](https://www.sktime.net/en/stable/related_software.html) page points to a broken URL that returns a 404 error.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Go to https://www.sktime.net/en/stable/related_software.html\n2. Scroll to the **Acknowledgements** section at the bottom\n3. Click the \"here\" link (which credits Max Christ for starting the list)\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nThe link should navigate to the original awesome time series list by Max Christ on GitHub.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nThe link redirects to:\n`https://github.com/MaxBenChrist/awesome_time_series_in_python/blob/main/README.md`\n\n…which returns **404 - Page not found**, with the error: *\"Cannot find a valid ref in `main/README.md`\"*\n\n## Possible Fix\n\nThe repository likely uses `master` as the default branch instead of `main`. The correct URL should probably be:\n`https://github.com/MaxBenChrist/awesome_time_series_in_python/blob/master/README.md`\n\nOr simply link to the repo root:\n`https://github.com/MaxBenChrist/awesome_time_series_in_python`\n\n## Environment\n\n- sktime docs version: stable (v0.16.1)\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f18fe98a-51cd-47e2-9aaa-06a1a0bd94d1\n",
